734555f-a.title: North (Hudson) River - River scenes - [Pier 84.]
734555f-a.folder: 12th Avenue Between 44th and 46th Streets (East), Manhattan, N.Y.

710777f-b.text:
Twelfth Avenue, west side, north from West 46th Street. The buildings that formerly stood at 47th Street have been demolished. In the basin at the left is to be constructed a new 1000 foot pier. This will be No. 88 North River and will be used by the French Line. This site is
enclosed in View 2.
April 10, 1931
July 23, 1932
P. L. Sperr
933 38NEE ~ 57 9
